Package eu.profinit.manta.connector.erstudio.model

Interface Mappable<T extends DataObject>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    CompositeDataObject, SimpleDataObject
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataObject, CompositeDataObjectImpl, SimpleDataObjectImpl
    public interface Mappable<T extends DataObject>
    Interface for getting information about mappings of objects that can be mapped to zero or more DataObjects.

    • Method Detail

      • getAllMappedObjects

        java.util.Collection<T> getAllMappedObjects()
        Gets every DataObject that the instance is mapped to.
        Returns:
        Every DataObject that the instance is mapped to. If there's none an empty Collection is returned.

      • getMappedObjects

        java.util.Collection<T> getMappedObjects​(java.lang.String objectName)
        Gets every DataObject that the instance is mapped to and its DataObject.getName() is equal to objectName
        Parameters:
        objectName - Name that to search the mapped objects to be added to result by.
        Returns:
        Every DataObject that the instance is mapped to and its DataObject.getName() is equal to objectName. If there's none an empty Collection is returned.

      • isMappedTo

        boolean isMappedTo​(T object)
        Decides whether the instance is mapped to object or not.
        Parameters:
        object - object to find in the instance's mappings.
        Returns:
        true if the object is mapped to the instance, otherwise false.

      • hasMappings

        boolean hasMappings()
        Decides whether the instance is mapped to at least one DataObject.
        Returns:
        true if the instance is mapped to at least one DataObject, otherwise false.
